caller_intent: The caller (Lina) is clarifying discrepancies between two homeowners insurance quotes, specifically the dwelling value ($340,000 vs. $302,000), and seeking confirmation on whether the value can be adjusted downward.
resolution_steps: Agent Cecilia explains the dwelling value is calculated using a system that considers home details (square footage, construction type, rooms, etc.).
Cecilia verifies specific home attributes with Lina (e.g., basement status, fireplace removal, heating type, flooring materials).
Cecilia confirms the system's calculated value cannot be manually lowered below $340,000 but adjusts some details, resulting in a slightly higher estimate ($340,509).
Cecilia highlights the quote's benefits (flood coverage, equipment breakdown coverage with $500 deductible).
systems_referenced: Internal insurance quoting system (replacement cost estimator)
summary: Agent Cecilia clarifies a homeowners insurance quote discrepancy with a caller, explaining the dwelling value calculation based on home attributes. After verifying details, she confirms the system's non-negotiable value but highlights the quote's coverage benefits. The caller agrees to proceed and will send the quote to finance for escrow.
